dependency_management EXPANSION (P1)
    ├── DEPENDS ON: existing dependency_management content (additive)
    └── COORDINATES WITH: security_maintenance (shared CVE monitoring)
```

**COMPLEXITY RATINGS**

| Skill | Complexity | Rationale |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| operational_readiness_gate | M (half-day) | Primarily a checklist-orchestration skill. Requires mapping all Phase 6 output artifacts. Medium complexity because it must know about all adjacent phase outputs. |
| incident_response_operations | L (full-day) | Most complex skill in the phase. Requires: active incident process design, post-mortem template, action item tracking integration, recurring calendar definition, on-call rotation templates, and post-mortem archive structure. |
| slo_sla_management | M (half-day) | SLO definition templates are well-established (Google SRE Book). Error budget math is formulaic. Main complexity is the decision policy and DORA integration. |
| security_maintenance | M (half-day) | Combines CVE workflow, patch schedules, and secret rotation into a single skill. Complexity is in the breadth, not depth — each section is procedural. |
| capacity_planning_and_performance | M (half-day) | Baseline definition and trend analysis are procedural. Complexity is in providing ecosystem-agnostic guidance (cloud-provider-specific queries vary). |
| dependency_management EXPANSION | S (1-2 hours) | Additive to existing skill. Each ecosystem section follows same pattern as the npm section. Primarily research and template work. |

